Patient Descriptions: Patient 1: A 40-year-old individual diagnosed with Type 2 Diabetes. This patient, leading a sedentary lifestyle, experiences frequent urination, increased thirst, and fatigue. They have a family history of diabetes, with both parents having the condition. Despite being a non-smoker, they struggle with maintaining a healthy diet. Their BMI is 32. The prescribed medication plan includes Metformin (1000 mg/day) to manage blood sugar levels, and lifestyle modifications focus on incorporating regular physical activity and dietary changes for effective diabetes control.
Lifestyle Changes: Patient advised to engage in 30 minutes of moderate-intensity exercise at least five times a week. Follow-up in three months to assess lifestyle changes and medication effectiveness.

Patient Descriptions: Patient 2: A 55-year-old active individual managing Type 2 Diabetes with Acarbose, an alpha-glucosidase inhibitor. Despite a busy lifestyle, they maintain a balanced diet and have successfully avoided smoking. The symptoms of frequent urination, increased thirst, and fatigue have significantly improved with this medication. Their BMI is 28, and lifestyle modifications include continued physical activity and dietary adjustments to support blood sugar control.
Lifestyle Changes: Patient encouraged to maintain an active lifestyle and adhere to a balanced diet. Follow-up in two months for a comprehensive review of lifestyle changes and medication effectiveness.

Patient Descriptions: Patient 3: This 48-year-old patient with Type 2 Diabetes benefits from Pioglitazone, a thiazolidinedione, to enhance insulin sensitivity. Leading a moderately active lifestyle, they have a history of diabetic retinopathy. Non-smoker and following a balanced diet, the patient's BMI is 31. Regular eye check-ups and maintaining blood sugar control are emphasized in their treatment plan.
Lifestyle Changes: Patient advised to undergo regular eye check-ups every six months to monitor diabetic retinopathy. Follow-up in four months to assess medication effectiveness and lifestyle changes.
